# RulesMCP — Active Rules

## Languages detected
- Rust (RulesMCP binary)
- Bash (install scripts)

## Active Rust CLI Rules

### Global
- `global/startup.md` — mandatory session checklist
- `global/initialize.md` — project init sequence
- `global/topology.md` — layer-tag type naming (_adp/_core/_x etc.)
- `global/file-limits.md` — file size limits (max 2000 lines per file)
- `global/nesting.md` — brace depth limits (max 5)
- `global/tech-debt.md` — no TODO/FIXME/HACK comments

### Rust
- `rust/README.md` — Modern Rust 2021 idioms, Result types, no panic in lib code
- `rust/modules.md` — one module per file (no nested mod blocks)
- `rust/docs.md` — `///` doc comments required on all pub items
- `rust/errors.md` — Result + thiserror, no unwrap
- `rust/naming.md` — layer-tag suffix (_core/_adp/_x), bool prefix is_/has_
- `rust/constants.md` — no magic numbers, use named consts
- `rust/ownership.md` — Arc/Rc, clone-spam awareness
- `rust/threading.md` — no fire-and-forget, tokio::spawn comment

## MCP Tools Topology

| Layer | Module | Type |
|-------|--------|------|
| app | main.rs | Entry point, bootstrap |
| adapter | adapter.rs | MCP tools, interface |
| core | core.rs | Registry, search, scoring |
| shared | shared.rs | Entry_x, types, utils |
| pal | repo.rs | Git ops, cache dir |

## Naming Convention

Public types carry layer suffix:
- `Registry_core` — core layer
- `RulesMcpServer` (adapter) — note: struct, no suffix required for impl block names
- `Entry_x` — shared layer
- Types in main.rs have no suffix (entry point is exempt)

## Testing Strategy

- Unit tests for Registry_core (search, learning_path)
- Integration test: load register.jsonl, verify entry count
- Manual test: `cargo run` → registry loads successfully
- MCP test: start server, test tool calls via stdio

## Pre-Commit Checks

None enforced yet (project in Phase 1).
